First off lets look at the odds of spelling the letter "H". There are 26 letters in the alphabet and 21 of those letters are consonant. "Y" can also be considered a consonant.

So the chances of spelling the letter "H" with RP gadgets are basically 1 out of 21.
That seems like a fair chance.

However, when you want to spell the letters "H" and "E" in that order to make the word "He" the odds are much much lower.

When we spell a random vowel with RP gadgets we have a 1 out of 5 chance of getting the letter "E".

So the chances of spelling "H" "E" with RP gadgets is 1 out of 105 because 21 times 5 equals 105.

What if we want to spell the letters "H" "E" and "R" in that order? We have to multiply again.

So we have a 1 out of 21 chance to spell "H" plus a 1 out of 5 chance to spell "E" plus another 1 out of 21 chance to spell "R".

When you multiply all of these chances, you know that the odds of spelling "H" "E" and "R" would be 1 out of 2205.

Now what if we want to spell "HERO" in that order?

We multiply again.

21 times 5 times 21 times 5 equals 11025.

We multiply this because we have a 1 out of 21 chance of getting the first letter "H", and a 1 out of 5 chance of getting the second letter "E", another 1 out of 21 chance of getting the third letter "R", and another 1 out of 5 chance of getting the fourth letter "O".

When you multiply these you get 11025.

In other words you have a 1 out of 11025 chance of getting "HERO" with RP gadgets.

Seriously I am not making this stuff up this is true math facts and the fact that over 300 attempts were made to spell the word "HERO" none were successful because the odds of spelling "HERO" is 1/11025.

That simplifies and estimates to 0.0009.

You idiots have a 0.0009 chance of spelling the word "HERO" and you continue to give in to this scammer that started this thread in the first place.

Also even if you idiots are lucky enough to spell the word "HERO" you really won't be getting those Hero days since the guy who started this scam could be lying.

Seriously ANYBODY, including ME can say "Play this stupied game that you have a 0.001 chance of winning and the winner gets free HERO days" and they could just be scamming.
